in that ss, we use that (1+max(left,right)) to find the max depth
so what that does is it first goes left side, checks the left nodes and right nodes, both are 0,0
so for left side answer is 1, for right side it goes till the leaf edge and traverses up.

int maxDepth(struct TreeNode* root) {
    if(root==NULL) return 0;
    int lh=maxDepth(root->left);
    int rh=maxDepth(root->right);

    return 1+fmax(lh,rh);
}